04:25.064 --> 04:26.998
Guess who.

04:27.066 --> 04:29.600
Um, Ryan O'Neal?

04:29.668 --> 04:31.602
Right.
Ooh!

04:31.670 --> 04:33.604
You're always right.

04:33.672 --> 04:37.575
Hey, what's that--
what's that you're wearing?
It smells nice.

04:37.642 --> 04:39.577
Peanut butter.
Oh, Michael.

04:39.644 --> 04:42.046
Oh, you're makin'
a peanut butter
and jelly sandwich.

04:42.114 --> 04:44.148
But, Gloria, you hate
peanut butter and jelly.

04:44.216 --> 04:47.785
Hey, Gloria,
you're-you're not, uh--

04:47.853 --> 04:49.954
no, Michael,
I'm not pregnant.

04:50.022 --> 04:52.623
Oh, good.
I still hate
peanut butter.

04:52.691 --> 04:54.625
Great.
Who's the sandwich for?

04:54.693 --> 04:56.627
Our little visitor.
What little visitor?

04:56.695 --> 04:59.130
Hey there, big fella,
look what I just made for you.

04:59.198 --> 05:01.933
A super-duper
peanut butter
and jelly sandwich.

05:02.001 --> 05:04.335
Hey, who's the little boy?
What's he doin' there?

05:04.403 --> 05:06.437
He's eatin' a sandwich.

05:08.040 --> 05:10.574
Mike, why don't you
go upstairs?

05:10.642 --> 05:13.411
I'll bet you have
some studying to do,
haven't you?

05:13.478 --> 05:15.846
Oh, no. I'll wait
till after dinner.

05:15.915 --> 05:17.882
Hey, you know, he's cute.

05:17.950 --> 05:20.218
Hey, you know who
he reminds me of?
Nobody!

05:21.787 --> 05:24.488
I mean,
nobody in your family.

05:24.556 --> 05:27.425
Oh, no.
No, that's good!

05:27.492 --> 05:29.827
No, he reminds me
of one of the guys
from school.

05:29.895 --> 05:32.130
Hey, ma, you never did say
who his mother was.

05:32.197 --> 05:34.132
Didn't I?

05:34.199 --> 05:37.201
I'd better go see
how the dinner's doin'
in the oven.

05:37.269 --> 05:39.570
It's doin' fine. I checked.
Who's his mother?

05:39.638 --> 05:42.807
Oh! Then I'd better
go upstairs
and make the beds.

05:42.874 --> 05:45.143
<i>Uh, you made them</i>
<i>this morning, ma.</i>
<i>Did I?</i>

05:45.210 --> 05:49.213
Yes. Who's his mother?
What is the matter, ma?

05:49.281 --> 05:51.749
There's a strange little boy
in the room, and all
we wanna know is who he is.

05:51.817 --> 05:53.751
Yeah.
Who is he?

05:53.819 --> 05:57.088
Well, why are you askin' me
so many questions?

05:57.156 --> 05:59.424
So there's a little boy
in the room.

05:59.491 --> 06:02.860
Is there anything wrong about
having a little boy in the room?

06:02.928 --> 06:06.030
Is there a law against having
a little boy in the room?

06:06.098 --> 06:09.000
It's nice having
a little boy in the room.

06:09.068 --> 06:12.803
And if you want me to answer
any more questions,
don't ask me!

06:21.246 --> 06:23.414
Gloria, what's with her?
I don't know.

06:23.482 --> 06:27.452
Well, stuck on the subway
for 30 minutes again tonight.

06:27.519 --> 06:29.720
Arch, uh--
let me tell you
somethin'.

06:29.788 --> 06:33.491
The way your mayor Lindsay
runs the city's
transportation system,

06:33.558 --> 06:35.960
a workin' man
can get home for supper
around breakfast time.

06:36.028 --> 06:37.962
Look, arch--
daddy--

06:38.030 --> 06:40.999
I'll say one thing
for mussolini.

06:41.066 --> 06:44.268
He was no bundle of laughs,
but he sure could make
a train run on time.

06:44.336 --> 06:46.871
Look, arch, uh--

06:46.938 --> 06:49.907
wait. Ho.
Hey, hold your horses.
Hey, who's this here?

06:49.975 --> 06:52.176
Yeah, that's what we were
tryin' to tell you, arch.

06:52.244 --> 06:55.079
Well, go ahead
and tell me, meathead.
What's with the kid?

06:55.147 --> 06:58.149
Well, we don't know.
Mom said somebody
brought him here.

06:58.217 --> 07:03.654
I didn't think he grew like
a mushroom out of the chair.
Who brought him?

07:03.722 --> 07:06.424
Little boy, I brought you
a nice glass of milk--

07:06.492 --> 07:09.360
oh, Archie,
you're home!

07:15.300 --> 07:18.403
No, Edith,
I'm still at work.

07:18.470 --> 07:23.174
What you see standin' here
is merely a pigment
of your imagination.

07:23.242 --> 07:27.645
Edith, who is this kid--
Archie, I need
to talk to you.

07:27.712 --> 07:30.481
What? Gee, uh, who's
the little kid here?

07:30.549 --> 07:33.817
That's just what I wanted
to talk to you about.

07:33.885 --> 07:36.120
Well, whoop-Dee-do.

07:36.188 --> 07:39.857
First time in 23 years our
minds are "synchrosized."

07:41.393 --> 07:43.428
Who's the child?

07:43.495 --> 07:45.729
He's-- he's--

07:45.797 --> 07:48.966
oh, Archie,
we got trouble.

07:50.569 --> 07:54.405
Can't you answer me
a simple,
three-word question?

07:54.473 --> 07:56.407
Who is that kid?

07:57.976 --> 08:00.144
What's the big mystery?

08:00.212 --> 08:04.282
Oh, Mike!
Oh, Archie!

08:05.717 --> 08:07.651
Oh, Gloria!

08:09.121 --> 08:12.123
Oh, Edith!

08:12.191 --> 08:14.125
What is it?

08:14.193 --> 08:17.328
Well, you see,

08:17.396 --> 08:21.199
the bell rang, and I--
and I went and answered
the door,

08:21.266 --> 08:23.767
and there was
this woman there.

08:23.835 --> 08:25.936
Yeah?

08:28.073 --> 08:31.775
And she left the little boy
and sort of ran away.

08:31.843 --> 08:34.212
Wait a minute.
Are you telling me that...

08:34.279 --> 08:37.115
Some woman showed up here
at the door
you've never seen before,

08:37.182 --> 08:39.950
you don't even know,
and left the child here?

08:40.018 --> 08:42.587
Edith, I mean,
you don't know the person.

08:42.654 --> 08:44.855
Maybe that person
could be a kidnapper.

08:44.923 --> 08:48.326
That would make you
an "accessidy"
after the fact.

08:48.393 --> 08:50.995
- Ma, are you sure
it was her son?
- Oh, yeah.

08:51.062 --> 08:53.598
I'm sure
it was her son.
Well, how are you sure?

08:53.665 --> 08:57.201
Did she tell you that?
No, not exactly.

08:57.269 --> 08:59.069
Ma, what exactly
did she tell you?

09:02.174 --> 09:05.443
She told me
it was <i>your</i> son, Mike.

09:10.449 --> 09:12.383
What?
What?

09:12.451 --> 09:14.118
What?

09:14.186 --> 09:16.387
What?

09:16.455 --> 09:20.224
She asked for
Michael stivic
and just left him here.

09:20.292 --> 09:23.628
Ma, you have
to be kidding!

09:25.597 --> 09:29.133
- She better be kiddin'!
- Michael!

09:29.201 --> 09:31.602
That's your son there?
Michael?

09:31.670 --> 09:35.540
No, no!
Of course he's not
my son, Gloria.

09:35.607 --> 09:39.843
Get your hands
off my daughter,
you palooka,

09:39.911 --> 09:43.681
and head for
the Y.M.C.A.!

09:43.748 --> 09:48.319
Daddy-- daddy, calm down.
I'm sure Michael has
a reasonable explanation.

09:48.387 --> 09:52.022
Michael, tell daddy
your reasonable explanation.

09:53.258 --> 09:55.193
Well, I mean,
it's obvious...

09:55.260 --> 09:57.728
Some nut left a kid
on our doorstep,
that's all.

09:57.796 --> 10:00.398
No, no!
That ain't all!

10:00.465 --> 10:03.767
That kid was left
special delivery
for Michael stivic!

10:03.835 --> 10:06.937
There can't be more than
one of them in this world.

10:07.005 --> 10:10.374
Archie, all that proves
is that whoever this nut is,
she knows my name.

10:10.442 --> 10:12.810
I mean, haven't
you ever gotten anything
you didn't ask for?

10:20.586 --> 10:22.520
I'm lookin' right at it.

10:24.389 --> 10:26.857
Look, uh, Archie,
that kid--

10:26.925 --> 10:29.126
I mean, I would know if
I had a son, wouldn't I?

10:29.194 --> 10:31.395
I mean, look at that kid!
He doesn't even look like me!

10:31.463 --> 10:35.065
Except a little
when he pouts.
Ma, please!

10:36.568 --> 10:40.137
Daddy-- daddy,
Michael's right.
It's obviously a big mistake.

10:40.205 --> 10:42.873
Of course it's a mistake!
It always is!

10:44.509 --> 10:48.078
This is a mistake that he made
I figure about four years ago.

10:48.146 --> 10:52.416
And look at this.
His mistake is gettin'
peanut butter all over my chair!

10:52.484 --> 10:55.986
I'll get it off.
Oh, he has it on his face.

10:56.054 --> 10:57.921
Have you got a hankie?

10:57.989 --> 11:00.157
Michael, what are
we gonna do?
Uh-- uh--

11:00.225 --> 11:02.092
I'll call the
child welfare bureau.

11:02.160 --> 11:04.328
Why would anybody
do a thing like this?

11:04.396 --> 11:06.530
Who knows, Gloria?
Some stupid reason.

11:06.598 --> 11:09.867
Look. Here's a picture
of the little boy.

11:09.934 --> 11:12.803
We don't need
no picture of him, Edith.
We can see what he looks like.

11:12.871 --> 11:15.306
He's standin'
with his mother.

11:15.374 --> 11:19.577
Oh. His mother's
very attractive.

11:19.645 --> 11:22.179
Uh, I wanna report
a child leaving.

11:22.247 --> 11:24.948
Uh, a child leaving.
Uh--

11:25.016 --> 11:27.885
no, no, I don't mean
the child left.
The child is here.

11:27.952 --> 11:31.221
The mother left.
Uh-- yes, I'll hold on.

11:31.290 --> 11:35.526
Michael, here's a picture
of his mother.
Do you recognize her?

11:35.594 --> 11:38.296
Gloria, if I thought
for one second...

11:38.363 --> 11:40.331
That that boy was my son--

11:45.870 --> 11:48.205
that's Marilyn Sanders.

12:00.185 --> 12:02.052
<i>I mean, I don't</i>
<i>understand it, Michael.</i>

12:02.120 --> 12:06.524
In all the time we've been
together, you never ever once
even mentioned Marilyn Sanders.

12:06.591 --> 12:08.526
- Michael!
- [ Grunts ]

12:10.295 --> 12:12.296
Did you fall asleep
on me again?

12:12.364 --> 12:14.865
No, Gloria.
What makes you think that?

12:14.933 --> 12:18.502
I've heard every word
you've said... all night.

12:18.570 --> 12:21.038
Every single word.

12:21.105 --> 12:23.341
<i>Michael, look at me.</i>
<i>Hmm?</i>

12:23.408 --> 12:26.143
- We have some more
talking to do.
- More talking?

12:26.211 --> 12:30.981
Gloria, it's 5:30 in the
morning. You've said everything
there is to say... twice.

12:31.049 --> 12:33.183
You miserable creep.

12:33.251 --> 12:35.619
You said that three times.

12:35.687 --> 12:37.621
You're not funny, papa!

12:37.689 --> 12:39.790
Ohh!

12:39.858 --> 12:43.828
Don't say that, Gloria!
Don't say that!
You have no right to say that!

12:43.895 --> 12:46.697
And you have no right
to be that!

12:46.765 --> 12:48.699
Gloria--
well, it's true,
isn't it?

12:48.767 --> 12:50.701
I don't know if it's true!

12:50.769 --> 12:53.103
But Marilyn Sanders knows,
doesn't she?

12:53.171 --> 12:56.173
Gloria,
I tried to reach her.
Her phone was disconnected.

12:56.241 --> 12:59.042
There was no address.
There's no way
I can contact her!

12:59.110 --> 13:00.811
I thought you'd
already done that.

13:00.879 --> 13:04.014
Oh, that--
you!

13:04.082 --> 13:07.752
Even if it's true, Gloria,
I'm a human being,
and human beings make mistakes!

13:07.819 --> 13:12.690
But most people's mistakes
don't walk in the front door
and say, "hi, daddy!"

13:12.758 --> 13:15.125
Will you listen
to yourself, Gloria?

13:15.193 --> 13:18.962
You sound like queen Victoria!
What happened to the modern,
liberated girl I married?

13:19.030 --> 13:22.566
She became a mother
by special delivery!

13:22.634 --> 13:26.837
Look, Gloria, that--
that boy,
he can't be my son.

13:26.905 --> 13:29.172
I mean, it's practically
impossible.

13:29.240 --> 13:32.342
The odds are all against it.
You went out with her,
didn't you?

13:32.411 --> 13:35.513
Well, yeah.
I knew her,
but not that well.

13:35.580 --> 13:38.382
It--
it was only once.

13:38.450 --> 13:41.351
If I remember
my biology right,
once is enough.

13:41.420 --> 13:43.721
For fruit flies!

13:46.725 --> 13:49.493
With human beings,
it only happens that fast
in the movies!

13:49.561 --> 13:52.596
I don't care
where it happened!

13:52.664 --> 13:55.165
I just wanna know
why you didn't marry her.

13:55.233 --> 13:58.035
Because I didn't love her!
Then how
could you take her--

13:58.102 --> 14:00.037
because I liked her.

14:05.944 --> 14:08.045
She was... pretty.

14:09.147 --> 14:11.482
Thank you.
Oh, come on, now,
Gloria.

14:11.550 --> 14:13.484
No, I don't wanna hear...
You know I didn't
mean it that way.

14:13.552 --> 14:16.219
Anymore about her!

14:16.287 --> 14:18.221
What was she like, Michael?

14:19.758 --> 14:23.427
Well, she had a nice...

14:23.495 --> 14:26.296
Sense of humor.

14:26.364 --> 14:28.432
Michael, that's not
what I mean.

14:28.500 --> 14:30.968
Do I have to
spell it out for you?

14:31.035 --> 14:34.104
For crying out loud, Gloria!
On that subject,
I never gave grades!

14:38.677 --> 14:41.579
Look, Gloria,

14:41.646 --> 14:43.848
I love <i>you.</i>

14:43.915 --> 14:46.784
You're the only one
that matters.

14:46.852 --> 14:49.319
No one else ever--
ever came close.

14:53.925 --> 14:55.860
Are you sure?

14:55.927 --> 14:58.161
Sure I'm sure.

14:58.229 --> 15:01.465
Hey, before we met,
that doesn't count.

15:01.533 --> 15:04.635
I mean, we both
had lives of our own.

15:04.703 --> 15:08.071
You went out with other guys.
I never asked you about them.

15:08.139 --> 15:12.009
I figured... if you wanted
to tell me about 'em,
you'd tell me.

15:12.076 --> 15:14.812
Well, Michael,
if you really wanna know--

15:14.880 --> 15:17.982
don't tell me!
I don't wanna know!
Michael!

15:18.049 --> 15:19.984
<i>[ Arguing continues ]</i>

15:23.688 --> 15:25.623
Do you hear this?

15:26.892 --> 15:29.827
World war III's
still blazin' away...

15:31.029 --> 15:33.597
At 5:30 in the A.M.

15:33.665 --> 15:36.634
Geez, I gotta get up
in an hour, I ain't even
been to bed yet.

15:38.202 --> 15:40.137
I know.

15:40.204 --> 15:43.440
I thought I was gonna
be able to drop off
once or twice up there...

15:43.508 --> 15:46.076
In a lull in
the "hostililities."

15:48.046 --> 15:51.314
But then the kid
kept botherin' me.
Had me in a midnight shuffle.

15:51.382 --> 15:54.284
- What did he want?
- Water, Edith.

15:54.352 --> 15:56.286
Half the night
he was fillin' up on it,
the other half...

15:56.354 --> 15:59.590
He was gettin' rid of it.

15:59.658 --> 16:01.592
<i>Where are you going,</i>
<i>Michael?</i>
<i>I'm not going anywhere!</i>

16:01.660 --> 16:03.994
Ah, here come the lovebirds.

16:04.062 --> 16:06.496
Michael, you can't
run away from the problem!

16:06.565 --> 16:09.099
I'm not running away, Gloria.
I just wanna get
something to eat.

16:09.167 --> 16:11.234
Will you listen to that!

16:11.302 --> 16:13.804
If that guy was on the <i>Titanic,</i>
<i>he'd keep on eatin'...</i>

16:13.872 --> 16:16.540
Till the water come up
over his nose!

16:16.608 --> 16:20.477
You can't blame him
for havin' a good appetite.

16:20.545 --> 16:22.913
Whoa-oa-oa!

16:22.981 --> 16:25.849
This bird's got appetites
in all directions.

16:25.917 --> 16:29.086
Come on, arch.
Daddy, stop it!

16:29.153 --> 16:33.490
Somebody should've told him
to stop it before he become
father of the year!

16:33.558 --> 16:35.425
You stop picking
on Michael!

16:35.493 --> 16:38.261
Yeah. She's been doin'
a great job of that
all night by herself.

16:38.329 --> 16:41.198
And you shut up!
I don't wanna hear
another word out of you!

16:41.265 --> 16:44.101
I've come to a decision.
I've decided
to stay with you...

16:44.168 --> 16:46.103
Whether the little boy
is yours or not.

16:46.170 --> 16:49.873
Gee, it sounds like
you're stayin' with me
out of revenge.
No!

16:49.941 --> 16:52.442
I'm staying with you
because I love you!

16:52.510 --> 16:54.878
Well, if you love me,
you better understand
one thing, Gloria!

16:54.946 --> 16:58.649
I don't think that that kid
is mine, but if he turns out
to be, he's my responsibility!

16:58.717 --> 17:01.384
That's where
you're wrong, Michael!
He's <i>our</i> responsibility!

17:01.452 --> 17:03.386
Look, don't--

17:04.789 --> 17:07.424
what?

17:07.492 --> 17:09.593
He's our responsibility.

17:18.301 --> 17:20.503
Look at this here.

17:20.570 --> 17:23.641
A whole love scene
done in yells.

17:25.309 --> 17:27.477
Ain't that nice,
Archie?

17:27.545 --> 17:31.515
Ah, beautiful, Edith.
Well, I've had enough of it.
What are you gonna do?

17:31.582 --> 17:35.986
I'm gonna go upstairs
and try to get
20 minutes of shut-eye.

17:36.054 --> 17:40.958
The world keeps turnin' over,
and every time it turns
it leans on me.

17:41.026 --> 17:43.326
Come here, Archie.

17:43.394 --> 17:45.796
Look.
Ain't he cute?

17:45.864 --> 17:49.633
Yeah.
What if he is
our grandson?

17:49.701 --> 17:52.836
Huh?
Once removed.

17:54.806 --> 17:57.941
He can't be our grandson.

17:58.009 --> 18:00.410
Only person in this house
he's related to...

18:00.478 --> 18:03.547
Is casanovski
in the kitchen there.

18:05.116 --> 18:09.086
And I want the two of them
out of this house,
father and son.

18:09.154 --> 18:11.922
Archie-- shh!
Don't argue with me!

18:11.990 --> 18:14.324
Gloria, I love you.

18:14.392 --> 18:16.326
I love you too, Michael.

18:18.596 --> 18:21.565
What do we got to eat?

18:21.632 --> 18:24.267
Michael, why don't you
go in the living room
and relax,

18:24.335 --> 18:26.536
and I'll make you
a nice breakfast.

18:26.604 --> 18:28.605
Okay, thanks.

18:31.375 --> 18:33.310
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>

18:40.351 --> 18:42.086
Hi, Mike.

18:42.153 --> 18:44.955
Marilyn.

18:45.023 --> 18:47.958
You remembered.
Sure, I remembered.

18:48.026 --> 18:51.161
Oh, boy, did I remember.

18:51.229 --> 18:53.263
You, uh--
you look nice.

18:53.331 --> 18:55.432
Are you kiddin'?
I've been up
all night worryin'.

18:55.499 --> 18:58.401
I must look like
the wrath of God.
Where's Danny?

18:58.469 --> 19:00.470
Danny?
Oh, the boy.
Yeah.

19:00.538 --> 19:02.405
Uh, he's, uh, right here.

19:02.473 --> 19:04.908
He's on the couch.

19:04.976 --> 19:06.977
He's sleepin'.
He's fine.

19:14.152 --> 19:16.086
So...

19:18.957 --> 19:20.891
How you been, Marilyn?

19:22.060 --> 19:24.361
Great.
Just great.

19:24.428 --> 19:26.630
I mean, every mother
I know goes around
givin' her kid away.

19:26.697 --> 19:28.632
I'm in great shape,
ya dumb jerk!

19:28.699 --> 19:31.001
- I'm sorry, Marilyn. I--
- oh, forget it.

19:32.637 --> 19:34.571
Why'd you shave
your beard off?

19:34.639 --> 19:37.374
<i>[ Mike ]</i>
<i>Oh, uh,</i>
<i>i got married, and--</i>

19:37.441 --> 19:39.643
<i>[ Marilyn ]</i>
<i>Oh.</i>

19:39.710 --> 19:42.146
<i>[ Mike ]</i>
<i>Uh, how do you like it</i>
<i>this way?</i>

19:42.213 --> 19:45.315
<i>[ Marilyn ]</i>
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>I have to get used to it.</i>

19:45.383 --> 19:48.152
Well, before she gets
too used to it, Michael,
I think you better ask her...

19:48.219 --> 19:50.220
The $64,000 question.

19:50.288 --> 19:52.656
Who's the snotty kid?

19:52.723 --> 19:54.925
Shh! Shh!
Listen, here, you--
don't shush me!

19:54.993 --> 19:57.127
Did you hear
what she just called me?
Gloria! Gloria! Quiet!

19:57.195 --> 19:59.163
You're gonna wake up
the little boy.

19:59.230 --> 20:03.033
Uh, Marilyn,
this is my wife, Gloria.

20:03.101 --> 20:05.502
Gloria, this is my old--

20:05.569 --> 20:07.704
Marilyn.
This is Marilyn.

20:07.772 --> 20:09.807
Hello.

20:09.874 --> 20:11.708
Well, are you gonna
ask her the question?

20:11.776 --> 20:14.845
Uh, yeah.
Uh, Marilyn...

20:17.148 --> 20:19.516
Uh,

20:19.583 --> 20:22.319
I'm not, uh--

20:23.454 --> 20:25.388
no, you're not
the father, Mike.

20:25.456 --> 20:27.858
- Oh, thank God.
- What?

20:27.926 --> 20:31.094
- I didn't mean it that way.
- Where do you come off
puttin' down my kid?

20:31.162 --> 20:33.964
You couldn't father
a boy like that on your
best day you ever lived!

20:34.032 --> 20:36.900
[ Voices overlapping ]

20:36.968 --> 20:40.003
[ Archie ]
Will youse two pipe down!
Last time I seen you,

20:40.071 --> 20:42.206
youse was in
each other's arms.

20:42.273 --> 20:44.842
The battle
is still ragin' on!

20:44.909 --> 20:47.644
But now we see
a new platoon in the field.

20:48.847 --> 20:50.780
Who's this?

20:50.849 --> 20:53.951
Daddy, ma,
this is Marilyn Sanders,
the little boy's mother.

20:54.018 --> 20:55.953
Hello.
Oh, ho, ho, ho.

20:56.020 --> 20:58.856
The mother, huh?
Well, if you've come
to pick up the child,

20:58.923 --> 21:03.626
you can collect the father too,
and the three of youse trot off
on a honeymoon together.

21:03.694 --> 21:07.597
Daddy, Marilyn just told us
Michael is <i>not</i> Danny's father.

21:08.967 --> 21:11.468
Oh, no?

21:11.535 --> 21:14.338
Well, that's the best news
I heard all night.

21:14.405 --> 21:16.506
And it's a damn lucky thing
for you you ain't!

21:16.574 --> 21:19.409
-What is it with you people?
You all hate kids or something?
-Now, wait a minute.

21:19.477 --> 21:22.645
Now, just wait a minute.
Don't hit us with that
"hate kid" stuff.

21:22.713 --> 21:25.983
I mean, you know,
we didn't drop the child off
on the dead run.

21:26.050 --> 21:28.718
- It was you done that.
- Listen here, chunky!

21:32.357 --> 21:34.724
You think it's easy
to bring up a kid,
hold down a job...

21:34.792 --> 21:37.861
And look for a husband
and a father for the kid
all at the same time?

21:37.929 --> 21:40.430
Guys you meet today
bring you home from a date,
take one look at the kid,

21:40.498 --> 21:42.732
and it's slam, bam,
thank you, ma'am.

21:43.902 --> 21:46.669
You should write a letter
to "dear abie."

21:49.607 --> 21:52.175
You're a panic.

21:52.243 --> 21:55.178
My last kiss-off
was a month ago.

21:55.246 --> 21:59.216
This terrific guy,
as soon as he found out
about Danny, that was it.

21:59.284 --> 22:02.219
And then last week
I met this new fella,

22:02.287 --> 22:06.156
and I-- and I didn't want
the same thing to happen
all over again.

22:06.224 --> 22:08.491
So I thought if I could just
leave Danny somewhere...

22:08.559 --> 22:10.493
Until I could get something
going with this guy--

22:10.561 --> 22:12.262
but, Marilyn,
why'd you pick on me?

22:12.330 --> 22:16.466
Oh-- well,
I saw you one day in Macy's
with blondie there.

22:16.534 --> 22:18.936
Name's Gloria.

22:19.003 --> 22:21.871
I didn't mean it
as a rap, honey.

22:21.940 --> 22:25.442
Anyway, the two of you
looked-- you looked
kind of sweet together.

22:25.509 --> 22:28.511
Happy. Oh, boy,
is this gettin' corny.

22:28.579 --> 22:31.648
Let me take my kid
and I'll get
the hell out of here.

22:31.715 --> 22:33.650
Danny? Come on, honey.
Mommy's back.

22:33.717 --> 22:37.454
Come on, sweetheart.
We're gonna get your shoes on.
You all right?

22:37.521 --> 22:39.756
So you came back because
you missed him, huh?

22:39.824 --> 22:44.127
No, actually, I came back
because he swallowed
my diamond earrings.

22:44.195 --> 22:47.831
[ Horn honking ]
Tell the cab to wait.
I'll be right out.

22:47.898 --> 22:51.668
Tell the cab to wait.
She'll be right out, meathead.

22:53.371 --> 22:55.973
- Where's his coat?
- Yeah, where's his coat?

22:56.040 --> 22:58.508
Oh, right here.

22:58.576 --> 23:03.546
But why don't you keep
the blanket so you don't
have to wake him, Mrs.--

23:03.614 --> 23:05.682
miss--
it's missus.

23:05.749 --> 23:09.052
- Oh, I didn't mean that--
- don't worry.

23:09.120 --> 23:11.855
I was married
to Danny's father.

23:11.922 --> 23:15.592
But he wanted Danny
as much as you people.
[ Archie ] Hold it there, sis.

23:15.659 --> 23:18.395
You got some kind of nerve
sayin' that.

23:18.463 --> 23:22.832
You come into our house,
you turn the joint upside down,
you cost me a night's sleep.

23:22.900 --> 23:25.768
Then you're gonna stand there
and blame your life on us.

23:25.836 --> 23:28.138
Archie, be nice.

23:28.206 --> 23:30.440
Think of
the little boy.

23:30.508 --> 23:33.543
Don't be tryin' to make me
feel bad about that!

23:33.611 --> 23:35.745
What's the use of me
thinkin' about him?

23:37.548 --> 23:39.582
I mean, there ain't nothin'
I can do about him.

23:40.951 --> 23:43.887
You know, look, sis, we got
a little house here...

23:43.954 --> 23:47.557
And a family and, uh--

23:47.625 --> 23:50.560
well, I mean,
the best we can do
is wish you luck.

23:51.829 --> 23:53.763
Luck.

23:53.831 --> 23:56.333
And God bless us,
everyone.

23:56.401 --> 23:58.335
Right?

24:24.862 --> 24:27.364
Oh, I hope
that poor girl...

24:27.432 --> 24:30.867
Finds a nice husband
and settles down.
Sure.

24:30.935 --> 24:33.570
Well, while all of youse
is standin' around here...

24:33.637 --> 24:36.606
Dreamin' up them
charmin' possibilities,

24:36.674 --> 24:40.544
I gotta go upstairs,
change my clothes
and get ready for work.

24:40.611 --> 24:44.114
Daddy, before you go,
I think you owe Michael
an apology.

24:45.383 --> 24:47.551
I owe him an apology?

24:48.686 --> 24:51.288
Well, he owes me...

24:51.355 --> 24:53.457
Two years' rent.

24:57.861 --> 24:59.796
So we're even.

25:21.719 --> 25:26.123
[ Announcer ]
All in the family <i>was recorded</i>
<i>on tape before a live audience.</i>

